parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS control module can lead to poor braking performance, increased stopping distances, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: The ABS light comes on intermittently

and flashes; the brake light blinks; the ABS system activates unnecessarily while slowing down or stopping; poor braking performance; the vehicle's brakes may lock up; the handheld diagnostic system fails to connect and gives error codes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hand brake can cause the vehicle to roll and potentially lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The hand brake fails to hold the vehicle in place

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The frequent failure of front suspension control arms can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and costly repairs.
Excessive wear on tie rods can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and costly repairs.
Battery explosions can cause fires, damage to the vehicle, and injuries. Electrical issues can lead to malfunctioning of various systems, including safety features.
Power steering failure can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and costly repairs.
symptoms: power steering gear and rack replacement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Heated steering wheel failure can cause inconvenience and discomfort to the driver.

Leaking cam tensioner gaskets can cause engine oil leaks, leading to premature wear on engine components, increased risk of engine failure, and potentially causing accidents due to loss of engine power.
symptoms: Oil leaks from the cam tensioner area

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the fuel sending unit can cause the fuel gauge to malfunction, leading to inaccurate fuel level readings, which can result in the vehicle running out of fuel, stranding the driver, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: fuel gauge stuck on empty or full
